text: Suh Hyo-won or Seo Hyo-won (born May 10, 1987) is a South Korean table tennis player. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's singles event, in which she was eliminated in the fourth round by Cheng I-ching, and as part of the South Korean team in the women's team event. As of December 2018, she is the top-ranked female table tennis player in South Korea and ranked 11th in the world. ==References== Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of South Korea Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Table tennis players at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in table tennis Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for South Korea Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:South Korean expatriate sportspeople in China Category:Expatriate table tennis people in Japan
